Agency Worker Regulations 2010

As you are aware, the Agency Workers Regulations 2010 (“AWR”) entitle agency workers to equal treatment after 12 weeks in the same role with the same hirer with regard to pay and basic working and employment conditions with someone recruited directly to do the same job on a permanent basis.



Your obligations under AWR


From the commencement of the assignment, you are responsible under AWR for ensuring that {!TR1__Closing_Report__c.TR1__Person_Placed__c} is able to access all collective facilities that you provide (on the same basis as a comparable permanent employee) such as a car park, staff common room, toilets and canteen.  You are also responsible for ensuring that {!TR1__Closing_Report__c.TR1__Person_Placed__c} has access to information on job vacancies in the same way as a permanent recruit.  If you need any advice about this, please give us a call and we will be happy to help.


Our obligations under AWR

Supply Desk Limited will ensure that {!TR1__Closing_Report__c.TR1__Person_Placed__c} receives equal treatment in terms of employment conditions including pay, annual leave, working time, rest periods etc. after the 12 week qualifying period.  You have provided us with the following information as being the basic terms which would apply to the temporary worker had they been directly recruited by you to carry out the same role.  Please check to ensure that this is accurate.  If any of these terms change during the course of the assignment, please let us know immediately.



